item.title: [+582] MIT debuts fuel-saving "double bubble" aircraft
item.description: Researchers claim space-age design could cut aviation industry fuel use by up to 70 per cent. Researchers at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) this week took the wraps off two new aircraft designs, which they claim could cut aviation fuel use by 70 per cent and deliver similarly deep cuts in air and noise pollution.

item.title: [+538] Man Goes Home With "Total Artificial Heart"
item.description: For nearly two years, 43-year-old Charles Okeke has tried to live a normal life in the hospital tethered to a 400-lb. machine. Okeke was barely 30 when a blood clot destroyed his heart, reports CBS News medical correspondent Dr. Jennifer Ashton. He had a transplant and for 10 years life was good for this computer consultant and father of three.

item.title: [+530] Astronomer Copernicus Reburied 500 Years Later
item.description: Nicolaus Copernicus, the 16th-century astronomer whose findings were condemned by the Roman Catholic Church as heretical, was reburied by Polish priests as a hero on Saturday, nearly 500 years after he was laid to rest in an unmarked grave.

item.title: [+523] The 15 Most Spectacular Photos of Mars by NASA
item.description: Mars still remains as one of the most mysterious planets in our Solar System. Latest NASA's efforts to explore this planet have brought not only useful information about the planet, but also some beautiful and previously unseen breathtaking photos of beautiful Mars landscapes.
